The long-term relationship of IBM with consumers is equally advanced.
It was one of the first world companies to eliminate all discrimination, which gave it a great choice.
Concurs with the anti-discrimination strategy and current plan, according to which a woman, Virginia Rometti, will replace Palmizano next year.
She worked at IBM for 30 years; she is now a director of sales, marketing and development.
In the past few years, IBM has organized meetings, online brainstorms, where many future innovations arise.
No wonder there's a lot of ideas - there's about half a million people working in the company.
An Organization with a good reputation
The firm ' s strong position in business is ensured by a strong internal and external image.
